<HL>
   Business Brief -- National Bank of Canada:
   Holders of Record Sept. 17
   Will Receive Rights Issue
</HL>
<DATE>
09/06/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   T.NA
</CO>
<IN>
STOCK MARKET, OFFERINGS (STK)
BANKS (BNK)
</IN>
<LP>
   National Bank of Canada said it will issue one right for
each share held to shareholders of record Sept. 17. Each 10
rights entitle the holder to purchase one common share for 8
Canadian dollars (US$6.90) until Oct. 9.
   National Bank, based in Montreal, said it has about 119.5
million shares outstanding. If all rights are exercised
proceeds will be about C$95.6 million.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   In trading on the Montreal Exchange yesterday National
Bank closed at C$8.625, up 12.5 Canadian cents. National Bank
said Levesque Beaubien Geoffrion Inc. and RBC Dominion
Securities Inc. will act as advisers for the rights issue.
</TEXT>
